@node "Introduction" "Introduction - What is AMIgotchy ?"
@{fg shine}@{bg fill} Introduction@{fg text}@{bg back}
  This is the @{fg shine}first virtual pet for the AMIGA@{fg text}® computer.
  The pet must be fed, you must play with it, you must
  switch off the light when it wants to sleep, you have
  to give it some medicine, when it`s ill and so on..
  This is exactly that what was called »@{fg shine}Tamagotchi@{fg text}« at
  first (this name is a registered trademark of Bandai,
  so don`t use it!). Now there are tons of clones and
  some programs on other platforms. Even a Java(TM)-Applet
  exists. But as far as I know, there`s no real clone or
  even anything near to it on the AMIGA®, so I had to
  write one :-) .. here it is!

   @{fg shine}@{bg shadow}Enjoy it!@{fg text}@{bg back}
      - Felix
@endnode

@node "Features" "Features"
@{fg shine}@{bg fill} Features@{fg text}@{bg back}
  Some features of AMIgotchy are:
   · @{fg shine}first@{fg text} @{fg fill}@{bg shadow}virtual@{fg text}@{bg back} @{fg shine}@{bg fill}pet@{fg text}@{bg back} on @{bg highlight}the@{bg back} @{fg back}@{bg fill}AMIGA@{fg text}@{bg back}
   · @{fg shine}P.I.S.@{fg text} (@{fg shine}P@{fg text}et @{fg shine}I@{fg text}maginary @{fg shine}S@{fg text}ystem) - try to touch your pet and wait
