@node "Prefs" "The prefs - how to set AMIgotchy to your own preferences"
@{fg shine}@{bg fill} The prefs@{fg text}@{bg back}
  @{fg shine}Sleep from h(12 h long)@{fg text}
    Your AMIgotchy needs some recreation, so it sleeps 12h long. You can
    set here, from which hour of the day it should sleep (e.g. if you set
    21 h, it sleeps from 21 h to 9 h). This is useful for sysops :-)
  
  @{fg shine}Name of your AMIgotchy@{fg text}
    You can give your AMIgotchy a name. This name can be entered here.
    
  @{fg shine}Speed@{fg text}
    Set your prefered AMIgotchy-life-speed here :-)
    
  @{fg shine}Maximum Age (+-8 y)@{fg text}
    This mysterious oracle tells you, how old your AMIgotchy MIGHT get.. maybe
    it gets older or doesn`t even get 2 AMIgotchy-years .. DON`T kill it, if
    you have a low worth.. maybe you set a new record ?
    
  @{fg shine}Task-Priority@{fg text}
    If your machine gets slower when running AMIgotchy, set a lower worth and try
    again..

  @{fg shine}Volume@{fg text}
    The volume of all sounds can be set here.
    
  @{fg shine}Password@{fg text}
    Do you want to protect your AMIgotchy from "unauthorized" access ? Enter
    a password here, and you will be asked to enter it, when starting AMIgotchy.
  
  @{fg shine}Reset current AMIgotchy@{fg text}
    Resets your AMIgotchy, so you can begin from the start.

@endnode
